112
You have launched an Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud instance into a pulbic  subnet with a primary private IP address assigned, an internet gateway is attached to the VPC, and the public route table is configured to send all insternet-based traffic to the internet gateway. The instance security group is set to allow all outbound traffic but cannot access the internet. Why is the Internet unreachable from this instance?
The instance does not have a public IP address

113
