A customer has established an AWS Direct Connect connection to AWS. The link is up and routes are being advertised from the customer's end, however the customer is unable to connect from EC2 instances inside its VPS to servers residing in its datacenter. Which of the following options privide a viable solution to remedy meet this situations?
